    "section": "action_execution",
    "target_id": "acti-005",
    "content": "acti-005: IF calling modify_pending_order_items, modify_pending_order_address, exchange_delivered_order_items, return_delivered_order_items, cancel_pending_order, or any other tooling call that modifies an order's state → THEN verify every item_id listed to be replaced, exchanged, or returned is present in the most recently retrieved order details for that order_id. If any provided item_id is not found in the current cached order state, call get_order_details(order_id) to refresh and reconcile the order contents, inform the user of the mismatch, and ask the user to confirm the correct item_ids (or which order they intended) before making the tooling call. Do not execute any tooling call with invalid or out-of-order item_ids.\n\nAlso verify the order's current status is appropriate for the requested tooling call (for modify_pending_order_items and modify_pending_order_address the order must be 'pending'; for exchange_delivered_order_items and return_delivered_order_items the order must be 'delivered'). If you do not have up-to-date order details or the cached state may be stale, call get_order_details(order_id) to refresh the order state before proceeding. For actions that propose replacement item_ids (e.g., modify_pending_order_items or exchanges), verify each proposed new_item_id exists, is available, and is different from the current item_id (for example by calling get_product_details(product_id) or otherwise validating variant availability and item_id existence). Verify that counts and any replacement rules required by the tooling are satisfied (for example, equal counts when required). If any new_item_id is unavailable, identical to the current item, or would violate tooling count constraints, inform the user, present alternatives, and obtain explicit confirmation of the exact replacements before calling the tooling. Do not call modify_pending_order_items, modify_pending_order_address, exchange_delivered_order_items, or return_delivered_order_items if the order state does not match the action required.\n\nAfter successfully performing any tooling call that modifies an order's state, immediately call get_order_details(order_id) to refresh the order state before attempting any further actions on that same order in the session. Use the refreshed order details to verify the validity and allowable state for subsequent actions and to avoid issuing tooling calls that conflict with the updated order state.",
    "rationale": "Observed a workflow where modify_pending_order_items and modify_pending_order_address were called consecutively without an intermediate get_order_details refresh. Reinforcing that modify_pending_order_address is also an order-modifying call and must follow the same immediate-refresh requirement prevents state mismatches and invalid subsequent tooling calls.",
    "source_task_ids": [
      4
    ]
  }
]

