  {
    "op": "ADD",
    "section": "action_execution",
    "target_id": null,
    "content": "IF a return/exchange action will result in follow-up instructions or return labels being sent by email AND the user indicates they do not have an email address or cannot access their email, THEN before calling return_delivered_order_items or exchange_delivered_order_items: (a) check the user's account for an email on file via get_user_details(user_id); (b) explicitly confirm with the user that it is acceptable to send return/exchange instructions to the on-file email address if one exists; (c) if the user does not consent to using the on-file email or no valid email exists, offer alternatives: (1) escalate to a human agent to arrange an alternative delivery method for the instructions (call transfer_to_human_agents with a short summary), or (2) proceed with initiating the return/exchange only after informing the user that system-generated return instructions will be emailed and that they must contact customer service to arrange an alternative if needed; (d) if the user prefers the assistant to proceed and accept that instructions will be emailed to the on-file email, record the user's consent and proceed with the tooling call using the appropriate payment_method_id; (e) do not assume consent to use the account email when the user explicitly says they do not have or cannot access email.",
    "rationale": "In Conversation 1 the user said they did not have an email but the assistant initiated a return and stated instructions would be emailed without explicitly confirming use of the account email. The playbook lacks a clear requirement to confirm use of an on-file email or to escalate/offer alternatives when the user cannot receive email.",
    "source_task_ids": [1]
  }
]

[
  {
    "op": "MODIFY",
    "section": "information_gathering",
    "target_id": "info-006",
    "content": "IF the user asks about product options, variants, availability, or requests an exchange → call list_all_product_types() if you need to map a product type to a product_id, then call get_product_details(product_id) to list variants, availability, and prices. When presenting product variants or exchange candidates, explicitly surface each variant’s \"available\" status and present only variants with available=true as immediate, actionable replacements. Before asserting a variant as the \"cheapest available\" or otherwise recommending it, verify that the variant's available flag is true in the most recent get_product_details response; do not promote or present variants flagged available=false as available alternatives. If a variant is unavailable, label it clearly as \"unavailable\" or \"backordered\" and offer it only if the user is willing to wait or wants to be notified when it becomes available. If the requested product type is not present in list_all_product_types(), ask the user for a more specific product name, product code/ID, or additional identifying details (brand, intended use, or a similar product name) before proceeding; if the user cannot provide more details, offer to broaden the search to related categories or escalate to a human agent. If a product category is found but no suitable variants match the user’s requested attributes, inform the user the exact option isn’t available, present closely related alternatives with their availability and prices, and confirm whether to proceed with an alternative or escalate.",
    "rationale": "Agents in the trajectories presented variants as \"cheapest available\" even when tooling marked those variants unavailable. The rule must explicitly require verifying the 'available' flag before recommending variants and labeling unavailable variants clearly.",
    "source_task_ids": [
      2
    ]
  },
  {
    "op": "ADD",
    "section": "information_gathering",
    "target_id": null,
    "content": "IF the user indicates they have just added or updated a payment method during the session → THEN immediately call get_user_details(user_id) to refresh the account's saved payment methods. If the newly added payment method does not appear in the refreshed account details, inform the user that the system does not yet reflect the change and advise common troubleshooting steps (refresh the page, log out and log back in, wait a short time for propagation, or re-add the payment method). Offer to wait and retry the refresh while the user confirms the addition, guide them through adding the method in the web/app UI, or escalate to a human agent if the method never appears. Do not assume the new payment method exists or proceed with payment actions until the payment method is present in get_user_details and the user explicitly confirms which method to use.",
    "rationale": "In trajectories, a user added a new card but the system did not show it; the agent needed to re-check account data and provide specific guidance. Adding an explicit refresh-and-troubleshoot step prevents proceeding with payments using non-present methods and aligns agent behavior with observed tooling propagation delays.",
    "source_task_ids": [
      2
    ]
  }
]

