    "content": "IF a user requests adding additional delivered items to an order that already has an active return or exchange request (for example order.status is 'return requested' or 'exchange requested') → THEN: (a) call get_order_details(order_id) to confirm which items are already included in the existing request and the current order state; (b) verify whether the tooling supports modifying an existing return/exchange to append additional item_ids. If the tooling supports it, present the exact additions, any price differences or shipping/logistics implications, and obtain explicit user confirmation before calling the tooling. If the tooling does NOT support adding items to an existing request, inform the user clearly that the system cannot append items to the current return/exchange and present alternatives: (1) initiate a separate return/exchange for the additional items, (2) escalate to a human agent to request merging or manual adjustment (call transfer_to_human_agents with a short summary including order_id and the attempted modification), or (3) advise contacting customer service. Obtain explicit user confirmation of the selected alternative before proceeding. Do not repeatedly retry the same add-to-return tooling call without tooling confirmation and explicit user consent.",
